# UI: Prefer shadcn/ui

When choosing **UI components** or implementing **simple UI features**, use **shadcn** and **shadcn.io** as the primary reference and source.

## Do

- **Check [shadcn.io](https://ui.shadcn.com)** first for an existing component or block before building from scratch.
- Prefer adding components via the shadcn CLI (`npx shadcn@latest add <component>`) so they stay in the project and match existing style (this project uses **new-york** style and **lucide** icons).
- For simple features (forms, dialogs, navigation, etc.), look at shadcn docs and examples before introducing other UI libraries.

## Don’t

- Don’t add a third-party UI library for something shadcn already covers unless there’s a clear reason (e.g. complex data grid, charting).
- Don’t hand-roll components that duplicate shadcn components (Button, Card, Dialog, etc.) without checking shadcn first.

## Reference

- Components: https://ui.shadcn.com/docs/components
- Project config: `components.json` (style: new-york, aliases: `@/components/ui`, etc.)
